    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "Diagnosis": {
          "text": "First, try applying lateral pressure to the skin and see if it sloughs (\nNikolsky’s sign\n)\nThen, to further narrow the differential, consider wither or not the patient is febrile or toxic in appearance\nPatients with an erythematous rash plus fever are also at high risk for having a deadly diagnosis",
